### Core Logic: Provider Router (the key piece)

```java
// service/ProviderRouterService.java — THIS IS THE HEART OF YOUR BACKEND

@Service
public class ProviderRouterService {

    @Autowired private ApiProviderRepository providerRepo;
    @Autowired private ApiKeyRepository keyRepo;
    @Autowired private RequestLogRepository logRepo;

    // Maps provider names to their HTTP client implementations
    private Map<String, NutritionProviderClient> clients;

    public ProductResponse scanBarcode(String barcode, String deviceId) {
        // 1. Get active providers sorted by priority
        List<ApiProvider> providers = providerRepo
            .findByProviderTypeAndIsActiveOrderByPriority("NUTRITION", true);

        // 2. Try each provider (primary → fallback → backup)
        for (ApiProvider provider : providers) {
            try {
                ApiKey key = keyRepo.findActiveKeyByProvider(provider.getId());
                NutritionProviderClient client = clients.get(provider.getName());
                
                long start = System.currentTimeMillis();
                ProductResponse result = client.fetchProduct(barcode, key);
                long elapsed = System.currentTimeMillis() - start;

                // 3. Log the successful request
                logRequest(deviceId, barcode, provider.getName(), 200, elapsed);
                return result;

            } catch (Exception e) {
                // 4. This provider failed — try the next one (fallback)
                logRequest(deviceId, barcode, provider.getName(), 500, 0);
            }
        }
        throw new RuntimeException("All providers failed for barcode: " + barcode);
    }
}
```

